Maybe more than half. It's not very efficient of the nuclear fuel, but then again, there's so much energy available, that it's still enormously effective. If you try for more efficiency, you quickly start running into problems harnessing &amp;/or containing that energy. Besides, the blasts are somewhat directional. The propellant vapor is directed back at the ship, as the primary means of coupling the nuclear energy to moving the ship. See the article on N.S front page which has images from the new book.<br>
<br>
Interesting note here: read in the book; F.Dyson said that there is actually very little or no flash when bombs go off in space -the flash we're familiar with is actually entirely caused by air being flashed into plasma. The pulse unit blasts are nearly invisible to the eye, until the plasma piles up on &amp; interacts with the plate, then it glows brightly.<br>
<br>
